article.headline: Assumption 10, La Salle 7
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Jon Eisele kicked a season-best 49-yard field goal with just over two minutes remaining to lift Assumption to a 10-7 victory over La Salle on Saturday. Jake Beers set up Eisele's game-clinching kick with a 43-yard reception for Assumption (2-7). Eisele missed on tries of 35 and 23 yards earlier in the game. Herb Woodard (26 carries, 74 yards) scored on a 1-yard run in the second quarter for Assumption, which received a strong game from Taylor Humphrey, who went 17-for-34 for 268 yards. La Salle (2-7) tied the score 7-7 at the 6:14 mark of the fourth quarter when Dave Macknet scored on a 1-yard run. Two minutes later, Eisele booted the game-winner.
